Document: CenterContainer  
Path: godot/classes/class_centercontainer.rst  
Summary: Describes the `use_top_left` property and its associated methods for controlling child positioning in a CenterContainer.  

The `use_top_left` property is a bool with a default value of false. When set to true, it centers children relative to the CenterContainer's top-left corner instead of the default centering behavior. This property is controlled via two methods: `set_use_top_left(value: bool)` and `is_using_top_left() -> bool`. The `set_use_top_left` method accepts a boolean parameter to enable or disable the top-left alignment, while `is_using_top_left` returns the current state of the property. This setting affects how child nodes are positioned within the container, altering their alignment point from the center to the top-left corner.